    <text id="F3516T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>A doctor reports on John H. Gray's medical history and treatment.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head> 
                    Medical Descriptive List 
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-01-14">January 14, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Washington DC</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>patient was wounded at Chancellorsville May 30, 1863. Minnie ball entering just
                    above the p<del rend="none" hand="h1"/> cavity passing out in region of middle third of
                    fibula without fracture anywhere. After receiving his wound he was taken
                    prisoner and held thirty days during which time his wound received no dressing.
                        <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> he was convoyed to the 5th Army Corps Hospital where he
                    received daily attention for one month up to the time of his coming here. Since
                    when he entered here the knee was very much swollen and so stiff that he could
                    not move it. Employed irrigation and he is now moving about with partial
                        anchyl<del rend="none" hand="h1"/> which I have no doubt can be in a great measure <del
                        hand="h1"/> use</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
